Code Testing & Debugging:

JSFiddle – An online code editor that allows developers to write and test HTML, CSS, and JavaScript in real time. It is widely used for prototyping and sharing code snippets with others
https://jsfiddle.net

CodePen – A popular frontend development playground for experimenting with web technologies. It allows developers to create, test, and showcase interactive UI components and animations
https://codepen.io/

ESLint – A JavaScript linter that analyzes code to identify and fix errors, enforce coding standards, and maintain best practices. It helps improve code quality by catching potential issues early
https://eslint.org/

Prettier – A code formatter that automatically ensures consistent styling across JavaScript, HTML, CSS, and other languages. It improves readability by enforcing uniform indentation, spacing, and syntax formatting
https://prettier.io/